name: Neural Lace 'Bluefire' Net Ablation 960-10
description:
This biomechanical interface was reverse-engineered from a device designed to weave a neural lace webbing into a subject’s brain from a parcel of biohybrid nanotech, heuristically adapting itself to the user’s unique neuro-strata layout in accordance with their genetic makeup. 

Signaling measured in the resultant neural lace appears to aggressively screen ingressing data from mind-machine linked networks, producing a drastic yet pyrrhic boost in virus coherence.

Increases virus coherence for Data Analyzers.
Decreases virus strength for Data Analyzers.
